article.description: Eric Jamison Jr. had a career-high 22 points as Gardner-Webb topped Division II Coker 73-59 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Jamison Jr. leads Gardner-Webb over Coker 73-59
article.linkText: Jamison Jr. leads Gardner-Webb over Coker 73-59
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- Eric Jamison Jr. had a career-high 22 points as Gardner-Webb topped Division II Coker 73-59 on Tuesday night. Jose Perez added 20 points and 10 rebounds for the Runnin' Bulldogs (3-5). Nate Johnson had 11 points and Kareem Reid added three blocks. Chandler Lindsey had 17 points for the Cobras. Roy Ellis added 10 points. Williams Onyeodi had seven rebounds. Gardner-Webb matches up against Wofford on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
